Floral basket to Korean embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- King of Cambodia Norodom Sihanouk sent a floral basket to the Korean embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A delegation of the Ministry of Royal Palace of Cambodia headed by Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister, visited the Korean embassy on July 8 and laid a floral basket before the portraits of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Written on a ribbon of the floral basket were letters reading "Highest tribute to H.E. Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, President of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. Norodom Sihanouk, King of the Kingdom of Cambodia."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the occasion the deputy prime minister said that the Cambodian people would make all their efforts to further develop friendly relations between the two countries established by Kim Il Sung and Norodom Sihanouk.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Polish FM 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- General Secretary  Kim Jong Il received a gift from the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Poland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The gift was handed to the DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun by vice-Minister Radoslaw Sikorski who is leading the delegation of the Foreign Ministry of Poland on a visit to Korea.

Rodong Sinmun calls for great national unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Nothing can breaker repress the Korean people's desire and will to reunify the country through unity of the whole nation, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Stressing that the nation's might is that of unity and its destiny is decided by the unity, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are a homogeneous nation strong in patriotism and unity. They had lived for many years as one nation, strengthening its identity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In order to defend their national identity as a homogeneous nation and independently carve out its destiny, the Korean people should join the severed blood ties of the nation as one and regain its identity as a homogenous one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Strong driving force of the nation should be built up to reunify the country. To this end, it is important to achieve the great unity of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Great national unity should be achieved on the principle of national independence. Only then, is it possible for the Korean nation to become true master of its destiny and a great motive and decisive force for the reunification and prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As the trend of the times can hardly be stemmed, nothing can break the Korean nation's will for unity and reunification.

Documentary films 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Documentary films of national value recording the revolutionary activities of the President Kim Il Sung have been produced in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   More than 40 documentary films have seen the light over the last six years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among them is the documentary film "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Meets with Heads of State and Prominent Figures of Foreign Countries" giving a record of his external activities (parts 1-7). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The film tells the viewers that the President met with over 70,000 heads of party and state and prominent figures from 136 countries from March Juche 38 (1949) till the last moments of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It also records the facts that he made 54 official and unofficial visits to 87 countries for 685 days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Documentary films "The Great Life in 1994", "The Fatherly Leader Among Working Class" and "The Fatherly Leader Among Agricultural Workers" impressively deal with the exploits the President performed by energetically giving on-the-spot guidance to at least 18,000 units across the country for some 17,800 days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There are also documentaries comprehensively recording memorial meetings held in Korea and various parts of the world after the President's passing away such as "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Is Immortal" and the documentary film giving facts from his reminiscences "With the Century".

Kim Il Sung's work published 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's immortal work "On the Three Principles of National Reunification" was published in booklet by the Natun Bangla Publishing House of Bangladesh on July 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is his talk to South Korean representatives who came to Pyongyang to participate in the high-level political talks between the north and south on May 3, Juche 61 (1972). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the talk he laid down the three principles--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--to provide a great program for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The booklet in its preface says that the issue of Korean reunification should be solved not only in the interests of the Korean people but for regional security and world peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that the President set forth the three principles of national reunification which serve as a cornerstone of Korean reunification, the booklet says that these principles are demonstrating their great vitality as the days go by for their fair and aboveboard, reasonable and realistic nature.

Books helpful to education in revolutionary traditions published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Several publishing houses in the DPRK have brought out many books helpful to education of working people in the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The books make a comprehensive and in-depth depiction of the glorious revolutionary history and immortal exploits of the President Kim Il Sung and profound contents of the revolutionary traditions of Juche, a national treasure of eternal value of the Korean revolution achieved under his leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Worker's Party of Korea Publishing House has printed "short biography of the President Kim Il Sung."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the book the revolutionary activities of the President are divided into 12 periods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Souvenir memo-books helpful to the visitors to the revolutionary battle sites and historic places in Ryanggang and north Hamgyong provinces and the education in the revolutionary traditions have also come off the press. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Science and Encyclopedia Press Group has brought out "The Major Chronological Table of the Revolutionary Activities of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" (6) which deals in a chronological order with the revolutionary activities conducted by the President from October Juche 69 (1980) to July Juche 83 (1994), and the Kum Song Youth Press Group "The Reminiscences of Anti-Japanese Guerrillas" (4) for the Children's Union members of senior middle schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Among those that have seen the light are many books based on the revolutionary traditions, including those on the spirit of devotedly defending the leader displayed by the young communists in their struggle under the banner of "Down-with-Imperialism Union" and the struggle waged by the Saenal Children's Union.

Foreign figures visit DPRK embassies 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Foreign figures, including Sazhi Umalatova, chairperson, and Shashbiashbili, first vice-chairman, of the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia and the Minister of Information and Culture of Ethiopia, separately visited the DPRK embassies in their capital cities on the occasion of the sixth anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They laid floral baskets and bouquets before the full-length figure portraits of the great leaders Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and bowed to them in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, the President of the c.c. of the Lao Women's Union and the vice-president of the central committee of the Lao Front for National Construction, etc, visited the DPRK embassy in Vientiane. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They laid floral baskets before a picture of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il standing on Mt. Paektu and paid tribute to them.

Pothong Gate 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- The Pothong Gate standing on the bank of the River Pothong flowing through the central part of the capital city of Pyongyang is one of the historic relics listed as national treasure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The gate was erected as a western gate of Pyongyang in 586 when Koguryo was building the walled city as its capital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was repaired in 1406 when the wall was rebuilt and the present structure was built in 1473. It underwent repairs several times afterwards. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The gate is made up of the substructure and the two-storied pavilion resting on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The substructure, 7.6 m in height, was laid with trimmed granite blocks with arched gateway, 4.4 m in width and 4.55 m in height, in its middle part. The front of the gateway used to be barred by a solid wooden gate reinforced with rows of iron rivets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The pavilion is a loft building with crane-shaped roof of double eaves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As a gateway opening out to the northwest of the walled city of Pyongyang, the Pothong Gate was of great importance throughout the periods of the Koguryo, Koryo and Li dynasties because it occupied a vital situation both from the standpoint of national defence and of day-to-day traffic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In 1592 when the Imjin patriotic war was fought the Korean people and soldiers dashed in through the gate and dealt a crushing blow to the enemy troops, liberating the walled city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Solid and elegant in its architectural style, the gate adds to the scenic beauty of its surrounding areas. From olden times the gate has been called a gate to send off guests and prized by the people as one of the eight famous sights of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The ancient Pothong Gate is in good shape thanks to the nation's policy to preserve the cultural relics.

Three-point charter of Korea's reunification  supported in Russia 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Political party leaders and organizations of Russia participated in the international signature campaign to support the three-point charter of Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The signature paper was signed by secretary of the central committee of the Communist Worker's Party of Russia Yuri Terentiev, chairman of the All Russia Socio-Political Movement "Communists, Working Russia-USSR" V. Grigoriev, chairman of the executive committee of the Soviet Congress of Russian Workers, Peasants, Specialists and Clerks A. Nokolayev on July 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Also participating in the signature campaign on the same day were organizational secretaries of Kalmyk Republic and  Moskva, Yaroslav, Sverdlovsk, Tyumen, Tula and Veronezh regional committees under the Communist Worker's Party  of Russia, the chairman of the council of the Tyumen region under the Soviet Congress of Workers, Peasants, Specialists and Clerks of Russia, and the organizations of the Communist Worker's Party of Russia of 17 republics, territories and regions.

Rodong Sinmun on national independence 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries a signed article stressing that what is important in realising national reunification, the supreme task of the nation, is to maintain the principle of national independence, which is the core of settlement of the national issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There is no more urgent task of the Korean nation than to achieve national independence, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   National reunification is the issue of reuniting the bisected nation and achieving nation-wide independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The principle of national independence constitutes the core of settlement of the national issue because it is an idea of independence reflecting  the common demand and interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The north and south of Korea should carve out the destiny of the nation independently. Independence is the only way of the nation to live and achieve reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The issue of reunification calls for maintaining independence in the movement for reunification. The maintenance of independence makes it possible to settle all the problems in the movement for reunification in conformity with the independent demand and basic interests of our nation and on its strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean nation has the ability to resolve by itself the issue of national reunification, an internal affair of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Our nation, strong in patriotism and high in the spirit of independence, has bravely fought in defence of the independence of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   No one can break  the will of our nation to reunify the country in an independent and peaceful way and no force can block the vigorous advance of our fellow countrymen toward national reunification.

Month of solidarity with Cuban people observed 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 14 (KCNA) -- Papers here carry articles extending full support and solidarity to the just cause of the Cuban people on the occasion of the month of solidarity with the Cuban people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Rodong Sinmun says the month of solidarity will mark a significant occasion in manifesting the Korean people's firm support and solidarity with the just cause of the Cuban people and further strengthening the militant and comradely friendship and solidarity between the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Today the Cuban people are steadfastly holding aloft the banner of socialism, smashing every move of the imperialists to isolate and stifle their country, the daily notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The slogans "Motherland or death, we will win" and "Socialism or death, we will win" clearly show how strong the Cuban people's confidence and will are. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Cuban boy Elian's recent return to his motherland from his detention in the United States is another brilliant victory won by the Cuban people with a staunch will and spirit to fight for justice to the last despite whatever difficulties and adversities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Korea-Cuba friendship based on the warm comradeship and intimate relations between the great leader Kim Il Sung and the respected Fidel Castro Ruz is steadily growing stronger and developing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people will in the future, too, fully support the just cause of the Cuban people and advance shoulder to shoulder with them in the common struggle to defend national sovereignty and socialism, the paper stresses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, Minju Joson points out that further developing the friendship and solidarity and cooperative relations between Korea and Cuba is in full line with the vital demands and interests of the two peoples and greatly conducive to the common cause of the world revolutionary people for independence and socialism against imperialism.
